com.ostrichemulators.semtool.util

Class Utility

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ostrichemulators.semtool.util.Utility

  • public class Utility
extends Object
    The GuiUtility class contains a variety of miscellaneous functions implemented extensively throughout SEMONTO. Some of these functionalities include getting concept names, printing messages, loading engines, and writing Excel workbooks.

        public static void mergeProperties(Properties original,
                                   Properties newones,
                                   boolean appendClashes,
                                   String delimiter)
        Copies the newones to original.
        Parameters:
        original - the properties "base"
        newones - the properties to add to "base"
        appendClashes - when true, if both properties have the same keys, append newones values to those already in original. if false, replace the original values with the new ones
        delimiter - The delimiter to use when appending two values together

      • implode

        public static String implode(Collection<?> collection,
                             String start,
                             String stop,
                             String sep)
        Implodes the given collection, appending start before each element, and stop after each one, and sep in between
        Parameters:
        collection - the elements to implode. Object.toString() will be called on each one
        start - what to put before each element
        stop - what to put after each element
        sep - what to put between elements
        Returns:
        a string representation of the given collection. If the collection is empty or null, an empty string will be returned.

      • getExporterFor

        public static org.openrdf.rio.RDFHandler getExporterFor(String filename,
                                                        Writer out)
        Gets the appropriate exporter for the given filename. "Appropriate" means the file's suffix determines exporter. If no appropriate handler can be found, an NTriples one is returned. Handled suffixes (case insensitive):
        • nt
        • rdf
        • ttl
        Parameters:
        filename - the filename to determine the handler to use
        out - the output writer to use to create the handler
        Returns:
        a handler (always)

      • getInstanceLabel

        public static <X extends org.openrdf.model.Resource> String getInstanceLabel(X uri,
                                                                             IEngine eng)
        A convenience function to #getInstanceLabels(java.util.Collection, gov.va.semoss.rdf.engine.api.IEngine) when you only have a single URI. If you have more than one URI, #getInstanceLabels(java.util.Collection, gov.va.semoss.rdf.engine.api.IEngine) is much more performant.
        Type Parameters:
        X -
        Parameters:
        eng - where to get the label from
        uri - the uri we need a label for
        Returns:
        the label, or the localname if no label is in the engine

      • getInstanceLabels

        public static <X extends org.openrdf.model.Resource> Map<X,String> getInstanceLabels(Collection<X> uris,
                                                                                     IEngine eng)
        Gets labels for the given uris from the given engine. If the engine doesn't contain a RDFS.LABEL element, just use a URLDecoded version of the local name
        Type Parameters:
        X -
        Parameters:
        uris - the URIs to retrieve the labels from
        eng - the engine to search for labels
        Returns:
        a map of URI=>label
